  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2015-06-09", 
    "text": "Veterans' Survivors Claims Processing Automation Act of 2015\n\n This bill authorizes the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to pay burial and funeral expenses, accrued benefits, dependency and indemnity compensation, and non-service connected disability or death pension amounts to a survivor of a veteran who has not filed a formal claim if the VA determines that the record contains sufficient evidence to establish the survivor's entitlement to such benefits."
  }, 
